Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of determining dense semantic correspondences across objects and scenes, which is a fundamental problem in computer vision. The approach proposed in the paper involves treating semantic correspondence as a constrained detection problem, where an exemplar LDA classifier is learned for each pixel. This approach is motivated by object recognition literature and recent work on rapidly estimating linear classifiers. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper also discusses the benefits of LDA classifiers and their use in the proposed approach, which makes it relevant to the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper also involves convolution and graphical models, which are relevant to the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
